Infrastructure & Cloud Automation (AWS)

Situation
The client lacked standardized cloud infrastructure, and deployments were inconsistent across environments, leading to delays and configuration drift.

Task
Design and provision a scalable, repeatable AWS infrastructure for an e-commerce platform.

Actions
Provisioned AWS infrastructure using Terraform, including EKS, EC2 (Jenkins & Bastion hosts), IAM roles, and VPC networking.
Implemented Infrastructure as Code (IaC) to ensure consistency and repeatability across environments.
Configured secure access using AWS CLI and kubeconfig via a bastion host.

Results
Reduced infrastructure setup time from days to under one hour.
Achieved fully reproducible, version-controlled infrastructure.
Improved environment reliability, security, and auditability.
CI Pipeline Implementation (Jenkins)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Situation
Application builds and deployments were manual, error-prone, and lacked version control.

Task
Implement a CI pipeline to automate build, test, and container image creation.

Actions
Set up Jenkins on EC2 with required plugins and secure global credentials.
Designed reusable Jenkins pipelines using Jenkinsfile and shared libraries.
Automated Docker image build and push to Docker Hub with version tagging.
Integrated GitHub webhooks for automatic pipeline triggering.

Results
Enabled a fully automated CI process.
Reduced deployment failures caused by manual steps.
Improved release frequency, consistency, and reliability.
Kubernetes & Application Deployment

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Situation
The application required a scalable runtime environment with proper service discovery and configuration management.

Task
Deploy and manage the application on Kubernetes with production-ready configurations.

Actions
Deployed application components on AWS EKS.
Configured Kubernetes Deployments, Services, ConfigMaps, and Secrets.
Managed MongoDB as a StatefulSet with persistent storage.
Ensured smooth communication between application and database services.

Results
Achieved high availability and scalability.
Delivered a stable application runtime with minimal downtime.

